# Example environment for signals infra deploys and local client
# secrets. Copy to scripts/.env.${ENVIRONMENT} (e.g. scripts/.env.prod)
# and fill in real values. scripts/.env.* is gitignored; this file is
# the one exception.
#
# Variables are grouped into two categories:
#
#   HASHED KEYS (ends in _API_KEYS) — the server stores these.
#     deploy-infra.sh sources them and passes to the Bicep template;
#     the SWA app settings hold them; /api/daily etc. validate
#     incoming keys against these hashes with timingSafeEqual.
#
#   RAW KEYS (ends in _RAW_KEY) — the CLIENT's copy. The Logic App
#     sends DAILY_RAW_KEY as x-api-key; the sig CLI and MCP clients
#     send ADMIN_RAW_KEY / MCP_RAW_KEY the same way. Only DAILY_RAW_KEY
#     is consumed by deploy-infra.sh (Bicep needs it to inject into
#     the Logic App workflow definition). ADMIN_RAW_KEY and
#     MCP_RAW_KEY live here purely for your reference when copying
#     into sig's config.toml, mcp-bridge config, or curl smoke tests.
#
# Variables within each group are listed alphabetically for easy
# scanning. Pair each pk_<scope>_... raw key with its matching
# {sourceId}:sha256:<hex> hashed entry — both produced by a single
# run of `pnpm run generate:api-key <scope> <source-id>`.
#
# Extraction pattern — pull a single variable into a shell without
# sourcing the whole file:
#
#   KEY=$(grep '^MCP_RAW_KEY=' scripts/.env.prod | cut -d= -f2-)
#
# `^` anchors the prefix so commented-out `#MCP_RAW_KEY=...` lines
# don't match; `cut -d= -f2-` keeps anything after the first `=`
# including later `=` chars that can appear inside base64-ish values.
# Handy for one-off curl smoke tests or MCP endpoint checks.
#
# === Hashed keys consumed by Bicep / server ============================

# ADMIN_API_KEYS — comma-separated {sourceId}:sha256:{hex} entries for
# admin read endpoints (/api/summary via x-api-key). Optional when
# there are no CLI or automation consumers.
# Mint with: pnpm run generate:api-key admin <source-id>
ADMIN_API_KEYS=

# DAILY_API_KEYS — at-least-one entry required. The /api/daily handler
# validates the Logic App's x-api-key against this.
# Mint with: pnpm run generate:api-key daily logic-app
DAILY_API_KEYS=logic-app:sha256:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET — from the GitHub OAuth App
# at https://github.com/settings/developers. Callback URL is
# https://<swa-hostname>/.auth/login/github/callback. Invite the
# authorized GitHub identity as `signals_admin` via the SWA portal.
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# MCP_API_KEYS — optional. Same shape as DAILY_API_KEYS, scoped to
# /api/mcp. Leave empty to disable MCP authentication.
# Mint with: pnpm run generate:api-key mcp <source-id>
MCP_API_KEYS=

# === Raw keys for local client reference ==============================

# ADMIN_RAW_KEY — the sig CLI sends this as x-api-key. Copy into
# sig's ~/.config/sig/config.toml (`api_key = "..."`) or export as
# SIGNALS_API_KEY. Optional when ADMIN_API_KEYS is empty.
ADMIN_RAW_KEY=pk_admin_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# DAILY_RAW_KEY — consumed by deploy-infra.sh → Bicep → baked into
# the Logic App workflow's x-api-key header. Pair with DAILY_API_KEYS.
DAILY_RAW_KEY=pk_daily_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# MCP_RAW_KEY — what MCP clients (mcp-bridge, curl smoke tests, Claude
# Desktop / Claude Code) send as x-api-key against /api/mcp. Optional
# when MCP_API_KEYS is empty.
MCP_RAW_KEY=pk_mcp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
